  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d1e19">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definition</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation, <in:term>Act</in:term> means the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96106_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Election Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d1e34">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Ordinary ballot</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The form of ordinary ballot set out in Schedule 1 is prescribed for the purposes of section 86 (2) of the Act.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d1e43">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Write-in ballots</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e45">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>A write-in ballot included in a mail-in voting package must be in the form set out in Schedule 2 or 3.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e47">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>If the form of write-in ballot set out in Schedule 2 is used, text identifying the electoral district of the voter may be printed on the reverse side of the ballot.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e49">
        <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>A write-in ballot used for any other alternative voting option or for a voting opportunity must be in the form set out in Schedule 3.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 130/2023, App. 2, s. 1.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
